      • setParentSandbox

        public void setParentSandbox(String parentSandboxName)
        Used by the Hub Server to construct the response.
        Parameters:
        parentSandboxName - - Name of the parent HM Sandbox. Can be null or empty if this is a master HM Sandbox. Master HM Sandbox is the one without a parent. This name is used to create the parent HM Sandbox UID.

      • setParentSandboxUid

        public void setParentSandboxUid(String parentSandboxUid)
        Used by the Hub Server to construct the response.
        Parameters:
        parentSandboxUid - - UID of the parent HM Sandbox. Can be null or empty if this is a master HM Sandbox. Master HM Sandbox is the one without a parent.

      • getParentSandboxUid

        public String getParentSandboxUid()
        Get the UID of the parent sandbox for this snadbox. Can be null if this sandbox has no parent.
        Returns:
        UID of the parent HM Sandbox. Can be null or empty if this is a master HM Sandbox. Master HM Sandbox is the one without a parent.

      • isPromotable

        public boolean isPromotable()
        Determine if this sandbox can be promoted to a master sandbox.
        Returns:
        true if the HM Sandbox can be made a master HM Sandbox.

      • setPromotable

        public void setPromotable(boolean flag)

      • setHmProfileUids

        public void setHmProfileUids(Set profileUids)
        Used by the Hub Server to construct the response. Set UIDs for HM Profiles that are associated with this HM Sandbox.
        Parameters:
        profileUids - - Set of String objects that are HM profile UIDs. This set should always contain one or more elements. It should never be null.

      • getHmProfileUids

        public Set getHmProfileUids()
        Get UIDs for HM profiles that are associated this HM Sandbox.
        Returns:
        Set of String objects that are profile UIDs. This set will always contain one or more elements. It can never be null.
